X \subseteq \mathbb{R}^{n}
 X = \left\{ (b_{1}, \ldots, b_{n}) \in \mathbb{R}^{n} \mid \sum\limits_{i=1}^{n} \frac{b_{i}}{i} = 0 \right\}
X
\mathbb{R}^{n}
b^k = (b_1^k, b_2^k, \ldots, b_n^k) \in X
b^k \to b = (b_1, b_2, \ldots, b_n)
b_i^k \to b_i
i
 \sum_{i=1}^n \frac{b_i^k}{i} \to \sum_{i=1}^n \frac{b_i}{i} 
f:\mathbb{R}^n \to \mathbb{R}
f
 f(b_1, b_2,\ldots, b_n) = \sum_{i=1}^n \frac{b_i}{i} 
 X = f^{-1}(\{0\}) 
